choices.text: It took us two weeks to make all of the plans. We had to get all of the ingredients, cook it, and put it all together in a way that he would not suspect a thing. He was very surprised and he loved the dinner. He said it was the best birthday gift he ever received. It was nice to see him smile and be so happy. I also enjoyed spending that time with my brother. It was a special bonding time for us. My dad had always taught me that it is the thought that counts and not the price of the gift. I remember when I was a child, he would always make sure that I knew he loved me no matter what. He would give me a hug and a kiss and tell me that he loved me. He would also tell me that he was proud of me and that I could do anything that I set my mind to. I will always cherish those memories and the special bond that we shared. I am so grateful for the gift of life and the ability to experience such joy and happiness. I will always be grateful for my dad and the sacrifices he made for me. I will always be grateful for my brother and the love and support he has given me.
